The paper proposes a benchmark for big data processing systems, which involves distributed computing and scalability challenges. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of linear algebra and graph algorithms, which are common in database systems, suggesting cs.DB (Databases) as the second likely category. The paper also discusses the need for rigorous benchmarks, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of the benchmark in various programming languages, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
